  <p>
    Of all septic problems, a failing drain field is the one owners dread — and the one whose cost is
    hardest to pin down, because it depends on the ground itself. To understand the range, it helps to
    understand what the field actually does and how it gets into trouble, because that's what
    determines whether you're facing a contained repair or a full replacement.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/drain-field-repair-or-replacement-costs-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
